<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12094c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12094c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12094c"> 94(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> widow marry, potbeating</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Guerleskin, si une veuve se remarie, pendant toute la nuit de ses noces, les voisins lui font un charivari en frappant sur des chaudrons. Si elle est divorc&eacute;e, le charivari dure parfois huit nuits de suite. <br> <font color="green">[When a widow remarries in Guerleskin, her wedding night is disturbed by the neighbours making lots of noise by beating on pots. If she is divorced, the noise may last up to eight nights in a row.]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="RDTP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RDTP"><cite title="source">Traditions et coutumes de Basse Bretagne</cite></a> (1904) 355</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
